RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOT AS LUCKY AS US stalked the pace down the backstretch, swung three wide leaving the far turn, secured command inside the sixteenth pole and drove clear. STEP AHEAD chased the pace outside GREAT CALL, challenged that one in mid stretch and weakened late. GREAT CALL rushed up three deep to take the lead on the first turn, was taken to the inner rail near the five eighths pole, set the pace to mid stretch and faded. PERFECT PEACE , kept well off the inner rail, stopped on the far turn and was eased. BAND TOUR chased the pace down the backstretch, stopped on the far turn, eased up, was distanced but did cross the finish line.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PIMLICO RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 24000. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR THREE YEAR OLDS. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $8,000, allowed 4 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOCEPHUS broke sharply, secured the inside and set a rated pace, moved away around the turn, opened up after being roused in upper stretch, was kept to left handed asks past the furlong grounds then continued to widen under some hand urging late. SUPERSTITIEUX , urged off the pace in about the two path, worked between rivals leaving the three sixteenths and kept on willingly to gain the place. PRESSING CONCERN edged up three deep nearing the half mile marker, tracked the winner mid turn, was put to a solid ride soon after, stayed willingly past mid stretch then faded late. LET FREEDOM SPRING angled off the inside nearing the half mile marker and chased the leaders, circled four wide into lane but failed to respond. CAPTAIN CARDO lagged well back under a ride, came four wide for the drive, angled in late and failed to menace. ISLAND D'LITE , away alertly despite leaning in and brushing the gate, prompted the early pace two wide, eased back off the leaders nearing the turn, gave futile chase around the turn and faltered.

ENTRY.COMMENT: urged off pace 2wd, split horses upper, willingly, gained place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PIMLICO RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 24335. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $8,000, allowed 4 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JANE STREET , three deep tracking early on, dropped in a path and engaged the leader leaving the far turn, sparred under rating, shook clear after being roused in upper stretch, opened up under left handed encouragement and was kept alert to the wire. ELLIE VICTORINA , fidgety in the gate, was unprepared as the gates opened and found herself several lengths back, regrouped and was taken to rate, commenced a run leaving the three eighths, advanced three wide between runners entering the lane and kept on gamely to be second best. RIDE THE RAPIDS tracked to the inside of rivals nearing the half, was under pressure as the leaders got away past the five sixteenths, raced two wide into the lane but lacked a serious response. AZTEC BAY prompted the early duel while about three wide, steadied and altered out a bit leaving the half, came five wide for the drive but failed to rally. CORA'S CHOICE drifted out a bit at the break, soon corrected and disputed the pace to the inside of STORMIN' AMANDA, briefly went clear past the half then was taken on from her outside by the winner, battled with that one to the head of the lane, shifted out and gave way. GOOD STORY altered outward near the half mile marker and faded. STORMIN' AMANDA dueled outside CORA'S CHOICE early on, sustained an injury near the half mile marker, was pulled up around the turn and vanned off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHERIFF RONNIE drifted out leaving the starting gate, disputed the pace racing in the two path throughout and drew off late under urging. CATCHING STARS chased the winner racing in the three path around the turn, challenged for the lead near the eighth pole, failed to sustain the move and bumped AUSTIN FROM BOSTON when drifting out near the sixteenth pole. AUSTIN FROM BOSTON , lightly bumped by KEEN LOOKIN leaving the starting gate, circled the turn four deep, was well placed outside horses in mid stretch and was bumped and herded by CATCHING STARS near the sixteenth pole. ENERGY EFFICIENT broke a bit awkwardly, raced inside horses on the turn, swung to the four path in upper stretch and failed to rally. INFINITE SERIES disputed the pace with the winner while saving ground around the turn, remained along the rail in the stretch and weakened. KEEN LOOKIN bumped AUSTIN FROM BOSTON when drifting out at the break then was not a factor. HERE COMES RUSTY , checked in traffic approaching the half mile pole, gave way. Following a stewards' inquiry and an objection by the rider of AUSTIN FROM BOSTON, CATCHING STARS was disqualified and placed second.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: POGGIBONSI quickly went clear, dropped in to secure the rail and set a rated pace, took outside pressure from ANGEL ART mid turn, kicked clear of that one after being asked soon into the lane, opened up under solid handling in mid stretch and held firm while kept alert. MONEY'S WORTH tracked inside under rating then steadied briefly entering the turn, regrouped then eased out three wide into the lane, advanced between runners leaving the sixteenth pole and continued willingly to narrowly get the place. LITTLE JOSIE WALES stumbled at the break, regrouped and edged up four wide, continued four wide into the lane, closed steadily outside MONEY'S WORTH and just missed second. ANGEL ART broke inward and bumped with a rival, straightened and moved up between foes to track the winner, bid the engage that one mid turn, battled into the lane, stayed willingly to about the sixteenth pole then faded. POLICE WOMAN , five wide nearing the half, dropped in for the run around the turn, came back out leaving the three sixteenths but lacked a rally. PEACE OUT , bumped and shuffled back leaving the gate, angled five wide nearing the lane and failed to menace. HITCH A RIDE , three then two wide chasing, was floated out a path entering the lane, shifted back in soon after, lost her action with about three sixteenths to go, was eased through the final furlong and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PIRATE RICK was nudged clear early and secured the inside, met a challenge from BACKNTHEWOODS mid turn, shook clear of that one after being asked in upper stretch, opened up under strong handling in mid stretch, wandered a bit before being corrected then cruised home through the final seventy yards. BACKNTHEWOODS angled out after a furlong and tracked the winner, went after that one mid turn, vied into the lane, could not match strides leaving the three sixteenths but stayed on well to remain clear of the rest.
